##Form Initial Understanding

Based on the package imports in TaskManager.Java, I can say this project follows a clean Layered Architecture.

It keeps the data, the program's logic, and the saving system in separate, organized packages.
TaskManager.app: Holds the core business logic and controls the application behavior.
TaskManager.model: Contains the core data structures and domain entities representing a task
TaskManager.storage: Handles data persistence, saving, and loading task information.

##Technolgies and Frameworks

Language: Java
Build Tool: Maven to manage the project.
Storage Format: JSON to save the tasks.

#Main Components

TaskManager.model:
This component defines the core data structure of a Task, acting as the project's foundation by holding information like task names, deadlines, and statuses without making any business decisions.

TaskManager.storage:
This component manages data persistence by saving and loading task information to and from the computer's hard drive,i think it uses lightweight files like JSON to keep data safe when the app closes.

TaskManager.app:
This component acts as the central brain of the application, running the core business logic and
coordinating between the user, the data models, and the storage system to keep the app working smoothly.

